<br>
Years ago when I first started playing EQ, me and some friends started a guild on the Prexus server. It was not a traditional roleplaying guild per se, but we did tend to act in character. Although we were more than a little loose in our RP interpetations. We had a troll that was raised as an elf and still considered himself an elf (he was named Flowerpetal). We were a hard drinkin', partying kind of guild with high aolchol tollerences and low levels. We folowed the &quot;Great Flower&quot;, the forgotten god of Norrath and valued fun above all else.<br>
<br>
I was the guild leader (Ryshat Annklebiter) a dwarven warrior or dubious heritage. I was also the guild webmaster and scribe. Seeing as how our chosen deity had been overlooked by the chronicles or Norrath, it was up to us to bring his word to the world.<br>
<br>
For the sake of keeping old tales alive, I present to you the first in a (very short) series called &quot;Seeds of Wisdom&quot;. Please take them with a gain of RP salt. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
And please feel free to tell me to peddle my wares elsewhere if you don't like them.<br>
<br>
[edit] Oh heck, there are only three of them so I posted them all. If they don't go over well, we can always delete the thread.[/edit] <p>-----------------<br>
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474342">Grafire Forgedawn</a></b><br>
High Elf Magician - Firiona Vie<br>
