"Grafire is my master."</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grafireforgedawn>Grafire Forgedawn</A> at: 12/17/02 6:44:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grafireforgedawn>Grafire Forgedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/02 6:34:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=656.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.inktank.com/images/eZgrafire.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tale 1: &quot;The Creation of the Flower Jihad.&quot; (long)</span><hr size=1> One bright and sunny day, the Great Flower awoke from his long sleep high above Norrath where the Gods dwelled. The Great Flower rolled over and looked at his Great Alarm Clock (as all things Godly and owned by Gods are Great). Wiping the Great Eye Crust from his eyes he sat bolt upright and exclaimed <br>
     &quot;Holy Tunare! I've overslept!&quot; From his bed of roses, held aloft by entwined vines of grapes and figs, the Great Flower leapt. He quickly brushed his stamen and ran a comb through his petals before heading downstairs to the Great Kitchen of the Gods. <br>
<br>
All of the other Gods of Norrath were already putting their Great Breakfast Dishes in the sink and looking at the Great Flower with a great deal of distaste. All of the Gods except Erollisi Marr, The Queen of Love. <br>
     &quot;Good morning Flower&quot;, Erollisi said to the Great Flower. <br>
     &quot;Did I keep you up too late again last night?&quot; she queried as a playful smile crossed her lips. <br>
     &quot;E.M., you're da bomb! We were all like 'plickity pla-KOW' and shit last night. Girl, you rocked my roots.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Language Flower!&quot; Tunare spoke up in that motherly way she did at times. &quot;Let's not go into details at the table, ok children?&quot; <br>
<br>
The Great Flower was about to sit down to a late breakfast when he saw the other Gods moving about and leaving the kitchen with their hands cupped, as if holding something. The Great Flower walked up behind Innoruuk and looked over his shoulder. <br>
     &quot;What ya got there Inny?&quot; the Great Flower asked. <br>
     &quot;Go away. I hate you.&quot; Innoruuk hissed at the Great Flower, spraying him with spittle. <br>
     &quot;For Tunare sake Inny, you hate everyone. You're the God of Hate. That's what you do. Now how about you pretend to be the God of Answering Questions.&quot; the Great Flower replied, tilting his great flowery head towards Innoruuk's hands. <br>
     &quot;They are my followers. Tunare made them for me. And I hate them.&quot; Innoruuk hissed again. The Great Flower peered into Innoruuk's hands and saw a throng of small beings the size of ants moving about in his hands. The tiny beings were tall and short, male and female, pink and blue and all manner of shapes and sizes. The Great Flower watched them move about as he said, <br>
     &quot;Well if they follow you, you better not back up or your likely to step on them.&quot; <br>
     &quot;You don't understand. They are my followers. They will spread my influence across the whole of Norrath. I hate them, and they hate me.&quot; Innoruuk spat out. <br>
The Great Flower started to walk away when he replied, &quot;Yea, we'll I'm sure you and your followers will have many lovely, hate filled, dysfunctional family picnics. And be careful about that spitting, you're likely to drown 'em all giving them a pep talk.&quot; <br>
<br>
The Great Flower started to cross the kitchen towards Tunare and her cooking pot. The rest of the Gods were becoming more and more interested in their &quot;followers&quot;, especially Quellios, The Tranquill. &quot;You like me, you really like me!&quot; he was saying into his cupped hands when the Great Flower walked by and approached Tunare. <br>
     &quot;O.K. Ma. Where are my ..uh... &quot;followers&quot;, are they?&quot;, the Great Flower spoke as he cupped his leaves. Tunare looked at the Great Flower and made a 'tsk tsk' noise with her tongue. <br>
     &quot;I'm sorry Flower, there aren't anymore followers.&quot; Tunare told him. &quot;I've divided them up evenly between all the Gods.&quot; <br>
     &quot;WHAT?!&quot; the Great Flower exclaimed. &quot;What do you mean evenly? I'm a God. Don't I count?&quot; he asked with more than a bit of annoyance in his voice. <br>
     &quot;I'm sorry Flower, I counted the heads at the table and divided by that number.&quot; <br>
     &quot;What about me&quot;, the Great Flower's lower lip trembled. &quot;You forgot about me?&quot; <br>
     &quot;Oh honey, I've forgotten an entire continent until only recently, so don't take it too personally.&quot; Tunare said to the Great Flower as she pulled him to her arms and tried to comfort him. <br>
<br>
As the Great Flower rested his head on Tunare's shoulder, his mind swimming with disappointment he noticed something. <br>
     &quot;What's that? In the cooking pot?&quot; <br>
     &quot;Oh, those? Those are just leftover followers. They stuck to the bottom of the pot and I couldn't scrape them off. I figured I'd let the Great Dog clean the bowl.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Well can I have them?&quot; the Great Flower looked up at Tunare his eyes wide with anticipation. <br>
     &quot;I don't know Flower. They are a bit off since they were undercooked. Plus there aren't that many of them. Only a dozen or so.&quot; Tunare hesitantly stated. <br>
     &quot;Fine by me!&quot; the Great Flower said. &quot;Can I have em, huh?&quot; <br>
     &quot;Well, ok. Just be careful. They look like trouble if you ask me.&quot; Tunare reluctantly agreed. <br>
The Great Flower reached into the pot and scraped out the bottom, scooping up his half-baked followers in his leaves. His face beamed with excitement. <br>
<br>
The Great Flower went to the Great Kitchen Table to get a closer look at his new followers. As he sat down he had to cover his followers from Bertoxxulous, The Plaugebringer, who was sneezing into his cupped hands and apologizing profusely. <br>
     &quot;Sorry Flower. I just ...ah...ahCHOOO!&quot; he sneezed into his hands again. &quot;Gee, mine seem to be pretty listless. I hope they make it through the night.&quot; he murmured as he shuffled off. <br>
The Great Flower spread his followers out on the Great Table and looked each one over. He noticed a rather fat one running across the table, apparently intent on attacking the Great Salt Shaker. He picked up the fat one, since it was the easiest to see. <br>
     &quot;Hmmm. What are you?&quot; the Great Flower queried. <br>
     &quot;I'm an elf.&quot; the fat, green creature stated. <br>
     &quot;Your sure are aggressive.&quot; <br>
     &quot;I attack because I love.&quot; <br>
      &quot;Then I shall call you Flowerpetal. The avenging but loving disciple.&quot; the Great Flower decreed, and set him back on the table. <br>
<br>
The Great Flower then picked up one of the smaller creatures on the table. As he picked the creature up, a foul odor emanated from it. The Great Flower covered his &quot;nose&quot; and spoke to the creature in his leaf. <br>
     &quot;What is that terrible smell?&quot; <br>
     &quot;What smell?&quot; the creature looked around innocently. <br>
     &quot;That smell. Can't you smell that. It's horrible. Even Cazic-Thule over there smells better.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Oh, that? Well...that is my...uh...it's..it's my defense mechanism. Yea. Defense.&quot; the creature blurted out. <br>
     &quot;More &quot;offensive&quot; then defensive I would think.&quot; At this the tiny creature laughed and offered the Great Flower a beer. &quot;Here, have a swig of this. It's what gets me goin in the mornin'.&quot; the creature said as it offered an almost microscopically small goblet. The Great Flower accepted the teensy cup and put it in his mouth. <br>
     &quot;Hmmm. Not bad. I think I would like this liquid in greater amounts.&quot; <br>
     &quot;You and me both, brother.&quot; the tiny creature let out with another roaring laugh. <br>
     &quot;I like you tiny one. I will call you Ryshat, after our fun loving, but smelly dog here.&quot; the Great Flower declared as he placed the tiny creature back on the table, being careful not to startle him and cause another &quot;defensive outburst&quot;. <br>
<br>
The Great Flower took notice of two creatures talking ... planning something it seemed. One kept saying the words &quot;tracking&quot; and &quot;organization&quot; as the other kept trying on different pieces of armor and clothing. Seeming to constantly be upgrading. The Great Flower leaned close to the table and addressed the two creatures. <br>
     &quot;You two look like you know what your doing.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Hail beeyatch!&quot; the blonde one said. <br>
     &quot;We're here, want beer, get used to it.&quot; the other one began to chant. They quickly organized the others to join in and soon all the creatures were organized and singing. <br>
     &quot;Well, you two seem to be quite the little organizers. I shall name you Sdaasiil and Tensai.&quot; <br>
<br>
Just then the Great Flower took notice of another creature. This one caught his attention with his talking. <br>
     &quot;You, funny looking one. You sound different than the rest. Why is that?&quot; <br>
     &quot;Well, I'm not originally from where the others are from.&quot; he stated. <br>
     &quot;How is that? I got you all from the same pot.&quot; the Great Flower challenged. <br>
     &quot;Well actually, I'm from all the way on the other side of the pot. It's very snowy on my side of the pot and we don't like to fight, although we are known for making knives. My people are a puzzle.&quot; he rattled on in a funny accent. <br>
     &quot;Well, that is interesting. I will name you Armathion, which means 'weird one' in Godspeak.&quot; <br>
<br>
The Great Flower began to pick up another creature when he noticed one creature grabbed onto the other creature's feet. He lifted them both up and addressed then in the palm of his leaf. <br>
     &quot;You, you have been standing down there making a hell of a racket. What are you doing?&quot; <br>
     &quot;I'm singing. I'm a bard.&quot; <br>
     &quot;I'll say your bad.&quot; <br>
     &quot;No! A BARD. I'm a bard. A musician.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Well don't quit your day job.&quot; the Great Flower laughed. &quot;And who is this little hottie, one of your groupies?&quot; <br>
     &quot;This is my mate. We go everywhere together.&quot; <br>
     &quot;I'm got his big ass on 'track', shall we hunt it down and kick it?&quot; she asked her mate. <br>
     &quot;Ohhh, she's feisty. I like that.&quot; the Great Flower smiled down on them. &quot;You will be Eloquinn and Banwen, my little love lumps.&quot; <br>
<br>
For the rest of the day the Great Flower named and got to know the rest of his followers. Feykyn, Gregorio (yet another &quot;organized&quot; one who had his act together), Scard (another smelly, small one), Yulsek, Caelx (another hottie), and Gremkin. He learned all about them and formed a bond with them. As he scooped them up in his petals he walked past Innoruuk and slapped the bottom of his cupped hands, sending Innoruuk's followers flying in all directions. <br>
<br>
Innoruuk looked around at his scattered followers and said, &quot;I hate playing '52 pickup'.&quot; <br>
<br>
All of the other Gods were already on their way back up from putting their followers on Norrath. Who knows how long it was in Norrath time from when the Gods had started to spread their word to when the Great Flower eventually got around to placing his followers on the land. Ages probably. Anyway, the Great Flower spoke to his new friends one last time before placing them across the face of Norrath, ready for adventure and to spread the word of the Great Flower. <br>
<br>
&quot;Live well my children. Remember this, life is like a game, so have fun. Spread the cheer and make friends with the other followers and eat, drink, kill, and be merry. You are now the holy warriors of fun. You are the ... Flower Jihad.&quot; <br>
 <p>-----------------<br>
