"Who's your daddy?"<br>
"Grafire is my master."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grafireforgedawn>Grafire Forgedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/02 6:41:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=656.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.inktank.com/images/eZgrafire.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tale 2: &quot;How Ryshat became the leader of the Flower Jih</span><hr size=1> After some time on the land of Norrath, the members of the Flower Jihad had their first visit by the almighty Great Flower. He appeared to them during a festival whereupon he asked for the increasingly excited crowd to settle down and listen to what he had to say. He also asked for someone to bring him a brewski. The collected Flower Jihaders gathered around the Great Flower and sat at his feet ... er...roots. After a long quaff of a frosty brew, the Great Flower spoke to the assembled masses. <br>
<br>
&quot;My children, you have found each other and have united in the name of fun. The time has come to choose a leader from among yourselves. Someone who will uphold the ... uh ... moderately high standards of the Great Flower. This leader will be the voice of the Great Flower here on Norrath. When he speaks, it is as if I speak. You know ... like a sock puppet.&quot; <br>
<br>
A murmur ran through the crowd, the last of his kind since his people had been wiped out by the Trolls. <br>
     &quot;I gots em!'&quot; shouted Flowerpetal as he shambled off after the murmur. Flowerpetal easily subdued the murmur and quickly devoured him. The remaining Flower Jihad members looked at him, mouths agape in shock. <br>
<br>
&quot;What? They are a delicacy where I come from.&quot; Flowerpetal retorted, picking his foul teeth with a foot bone. Flowerpetal then whipped out a roll of Mentos® and held it up for the crowd to see. Eventually the crowd all gave Flowerpetal that &quot;Mentos Smirk/Smile&quot;® as if to say &quot;I'd bitch slap you into next Tuesday if you weren't such a sassy bastard&quot;. <br>
<br>
The Great Flower rolled his eyes and cleared his throat as Flowerpetal took his seat again. <br>
     &quot;I have a challenge for anyone who dares to be leader of this group. Who is up to the challenge?&quot; The Great Flower looked around at the assembled masses. Darting glances were exchanged amongst the members. Soft words were spoken, inaudible to the gathered crowd. <br>
     &quot;Oh come on,&quot; the Great Flower continued. &quot;Someone must want the job.&quot; The Great Flower looked around again. Finally the Great Flower sighed and said, &quot;You get all the free beer yo...&quot; <br>
     &quot;I'M UP TO THE CHALLENGE GREAT FLOWER!&quot; Ryshat shouted. <br>
     &quot;ME TOO!&quot; Eloquinn said as he jumped to his feet. <br>
     &quot;Hey, you beeyatches! I was going to volunteer!&quot; said Sdaasiil. <br>
     &quot;Imafuh fer bat foo!&quot; Flowerpetal mumbled through a mouth full of Mentos. <br>
<br>
&quot;Ok my children, those are enough volunteers.&quot; the Great Flower addressed the guild. <br>
     &quot;Here is the task I have set for you.&quot; <br>
The Great Flower gestured to a mountain range far off in the distance. &quot;That is the highest peak in all of Norrath. I want each of you to go to the top of the mountain and bring me back some evidence of your journey.&quot; <br>
<br>
The Great Flower lined the volunteers up facing the mountain as the rest of the guild looked on eagerly. The Great Flower then raised his leaf, paused to look around, and then dropped it down suddenly, signaling the start of the race. The volunteers immediately took to standing around, looking confused. Ryshat raised his wee hand and wiggled his fingers in a wave. <br>
<br>
&quot;What are you all doing?&quot; the Great Flower asked. &quot;Why aren't you running?&quot; <br>
     &quot;Oh,&quot; said Ryshat. &quot;Is that what you were doing? I thought you were waving at me.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Huh? Sorry, I wasn't looking.&quot; said Sdaasiil. <br>
     &quot;I thought he was trying to swat a fly away from his head.&quot; explained Eloquinn. <br>
     &quot;No. When I drop my leaf, that is the signal to 'go'.&quot; the Great Flower explained, with more than a touch of exasperation in his voice. <br>
     &quot;Ok, is everyone paying attention? Good. Now here we go.&quot; the Great Flower said as he once again raised his leaf, stared intently at the volunteers to make sure they were all looking at him ... and dropped his leaf. <br>
<br>
The contestants took off at a sprint , making a bee line for the mountain, and of course by bee line I mean something more akin to a moth. They zigged and zagged this way and that until they eventually made it over the horizon. After a spell, the Great Flower and his followers went about their business while they waited for the return of their proposed leaders. <br>
<br>
After about two hours had passed, Flowerpetal returned to the festival, wheezing and short of breath. After a while Flowerpetal was able to collect himself and addressed the Great Flower. <br>
     &quot;I have brought back a flower, from the vast fields of flowers found in the rolling foothills surrounding the mountain.&quot; Flowerpetal wheezed. <br>
     &quot;A flower?&quot; the Great Flower asked. &quot;I was thinking of something a bit more ...oh I don't know... ON the mountain.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Well, I was making good time once I got myself turned towards the horizon, but I came across some roving bandits. Of course I had to kill them. Then rest. I was on my way again when I came across some marauding Gnolls. Obviously I couldn't let them live, so I killed them. Then I rested. Once I got going again I came across a ferocious horde of fluffy baby ducks and ... well, you get the idea.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Yes I see.&quot; said the Great Flower. &quot;Well, good job ridding the land of evil ... and ... ahem ... cute little duckies. &quot; <br>
Flowerpetal immediately whipped out a half eaten roll of Mentos® and beamed a cocky smile at the Great Flower. <br>
     &quot;Yeah, right. That was cute ...once. Let's just wait and see how the others fared, sassy boy.&quot; <br>
<br>
After about three more hours had passed a small speck appeared on the horizon. The speck quickly grew and came closer, revealing itself to be Sdaasiil. Sdaasiil leisurely sauntered into town and stopped in front of the Great Flower. <br>
He sniffed over at Flowerpetal and said, &quot;Let me guess, did tubby here get mixed up and jump in the ocean?&quot; <br>
     &quot;No, I brought a flower.&quot; Flowerpetal piped up. <br>
     &quot;A flower? What a suck up you are.&quot; Sdaasiil snorted. <br>
Sdaasiil looked up at the great flower and reached in his pack. From it he pulled an evergreen branch and laid it at the Great Flowers feet. <br>
     &quot;Ok, look. This is a branch from a type of tree that grows about a third of the way up the mountain. Now I know it's not much, but I would have gotten further if I hadn't ... hadn't been ...&quot; Sdaasiil's stammer turned to silence. <br>
The Great Flower looked at him quizzically. &quot;Hadn't been what?&quot; the Great Flower asked. <br>
Sdaasiil gathered himself and spoke. &quot;If I hadn't been overrun by a retreating horde of fluffy baby ducks. It was horrible, they just kept running over me, biting me as they went. They were afraid of something. I've never seen baby ducks afraid of ANYthing! Their raging tempers were only fueled by their fear. They just kept coming and coming! A snarling, peeping wall of yellow terror! Oh the horror!&quot; <br>
Sdaasiil collapsed exhausted at the feet of the great flower. <br>
     &quot;I told you.&quot; Flowerpetal said matter-of-factly to the Great Flower. <br>
     &quot;Oh shush, you.&quot; the Great Flower snapped at Flowerpetal. <br>
     &quot;You have done well Sdaasiil, considering the circumstances. This branch is a fine trophy.&quot; the Great Flower said as he consoled Sdaasiil and offered him a beer. <br>
<br>
Many more hours passed as twilight danced across the sky. Torches were lit and dinner was served at the festival. Someone screamed at the edge of the gathering and the assembled Flower Jihaders jumped into action, preparing for a fight. <br>
     &quot;Woah, chill out!&quot; a shout from the darkness came. The guild members held in place as a figure stepped from the shadows. The firelight from the torches played across Eloquinn's face as he moved into the light. <br>
     &quot;Sorry about the scream, but Elo pinched my ass.&quot; Branwen said as she turned and backhanded Eloquinn in the chest. Eloquinn snickered as he rubbed his chest. He moved over to the Great Flower and reached into his pack. He handed the Great Flower a small bush. <br>
Eloquinn began &quot;This is a shrubbery...&quot; <br>
     &quot;NI!&quot; came a cry from the crowd. <br>
     &quot;Shhhh.&quot; replied another voice. <br>
     &quot;A shrubbery from the side of the mountain, where vegetation grows sparse.&quot; Eloquinn continued. &quot;I had to wrestle it away from a tired and wheezing baby duck. Tired as he was, he put up quite a fight. I finally had to use my musical abilities to subdue him. I hit him with my drum.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Very good.&quot; said the Great Flower. &quot;You almost made it to the top of the mountain. What stopped you?&quot; <br>
     &quot;I broke my drum.&quot; Eloquinn stated. <br>
The Great Flower looked at him quizically. Eloquinn rolled his eyes and continued, &quot;Do you really think I'm gonna run my ass up some mountain with no Selo's Accelerando? I think not.&quot; Eloquinn responded. He then went over to Branwen and sat down. <br>
     &quot;That leaves only one left.&quot; proclaimed the Great Flower. <br>
<br>
Many more hours had passed as the festival went well into the night. As the revelries began to die down and most gave up hope for the final contestant, the Great Flower gathered the Flower Jihaders around himself. <br>
     &quot;Well my friends, it looks as if everyone who is going to return, has returned. Before everyone goes home for the night I think it's time to announce a winner. Since Eloquinn so bravely wrestled a shrubbery from a tired, albeit vicious baby duck, high atop the mountain, I declare him...&quot; <br>
     &quot;HOLD IT!&quot; a voice boomed from somewhere. The crowd parted to reveal Ryshat, standing defiantly in the center of the gathering. <br>
     &quot;I think I'm the man you're looking for.&quot; exclaimed Ryshat. <br>
     &quot;Oh really Ryshat? Please, do tell.&quot; the Great Flower said. &quot;I don't see you carrying anything?&quot; <br>
     &quot;I have been to the top of the mountain, where nothing can grow on it's rocky face. I have seen the whole of Norrath laid out before me. I have seen the sun set on the mountains in the distance. New mountains, representing new challenges. Each one bigger than the last. It has taught me that though our journey will forever continue, there will be mountain highs and valley lows and there will always be beauty and enjoyment to be had.&quot; <br>
The crowd stood in stunned silence. Applause from the crowd grew slowly and eventually became a wave of sound. The guild members picked Ryshat up on their shoulders and carried him around in triumph, whooping and hollering. Eventually things quieted down and the Great Flower was able to speak. <br>
     &quot;Well done small warrior. You have proven you are indeed the man I am looking for.&quot; <br>
Ryshat beamed a smile and looked around at the crowd. <br>
     &quot;EXCEPT ...&quot; continued the Great Flower. &quot;For the fact that in the rather staggering start of the race, I watched you stagger yourself right into that tavern over there. Jeez, I could even hear you belching and laughing from way the hell over here.&quot; Ryshat looked around again at the stunned crowd, their mouths agape in astonishment. He shifted uneasily from side to side, looked up at the Great Flower, and cleared his throat. <br>
     &quot;I brought you a keg.&quot; he timidly said as he produced a wooden barrel from behind his back and held it up to the Great Flower. <br>
The Great Flower stared him long and hard. A small smile formed at the corners of his mouth and spread across his face. <br>
     &quot;DUDE, THOU ROCK!&quot; the Great Flower exclaimed. &quot;You sure know how to bullshit. I think I have found the right man for the job.&quot; <br>
     &quot;Thank Tunare.&quot; said Ryshat with relief in his voice. &quot;No way in hell was I going into those mountains with all those ravenous baby ducks roaming about. That is one little yellow blood bath I could do without.&quot; <br>
     &quot;How about a regular bath? Ever considered one of those?&quot; the Great Flower joked as he poked Ryshat in the ribs. <br>
<br>
After sharing a laugh with Ryshat and wiping flecks of beer foam from his face, the Great Flower stood and proclaimed to the assembled masses, <br>
     &quot;From this day forth, the voice of the Great Flower shall be known as Ryshat. From his lips will pass my wisdom.&quot; At which point Ryshat let loose with a rather reverberating belch. <br>
<br>
     &quot;Dude, say it, don't spray it.&quot; the Great Flower responded.<br>
